### OrderPilot Core V1 Investor Demo Walkthrough
### Runnable against the deterministic local seed from scripts/seed-local-demo.ps1.
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@tenantId = 11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111
@productId = 44444444-4444-4444-8444-444444444444
@locationId = 33333333-3333-4333-8333-333333333333

### Seeded labels for operator narration:
### customerExternalRef/accountCode = CUST-001
### productSku = PAD-OE-04465
### locationCode = WH-ALM

### 1. Telegram RFQ intake
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/bot/telegram/webhook
X-Tenant-Id: {{tenantId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "update_id": 91001,
  "message": {
    "message_id": 7001,
    "chat": { "id": 450001 },
    "text": "Need 2 EA PAD-OE-04465 brake pads for Toyota Camry 2018, wholesale, Almaty."
  }
}

### Expected: RFQ_REQUEST, requiresHumanReview=true, createdRfqDraftId present.

### 2. Unknown message handoff
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/bot/telegram/webhook
X-Tenant-Id: {{tenantId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "update_id": 91002,
  "message": {
    "message_id": 7002,
    "chat": { "id": 450001 },
    "text": "Can you check the thing we discussed last time?"
  }
}

### Expected: UNKNOWN, requiresHumanReview=true, no quote/order/master-data mutation.

### 3. Run inventory reconciliation
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/reconciliation/inventory/run
X-Tenant-Id: {{tenantId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productId": "{{productId}}",
  "locationId": "{{locationId}}"
}

### Expected: expectedStock=116, actualStock=100, mismatchQuantity=-16, severity=HIGH.

### 4. Fetch reconciliation cases
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/reconciliation/cases?page=0&size=50
X-Tenant-Id: {{tenantId}}

### Expected: one OPEN high-severity reconciliation case for the demo product/location.

### 5. Fetch commerce analytics summary
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/analytics/commerce/summary
X-Tenant-Id: {{tenantId}}
X-OrderPilot-Permissions: ANALYTICS_READ

### Expected: totalBotRfqRequests=1, openReconciliationCases=1, highSeverityReconciliationCases=1, channelBreakdown.TELEGRAM=2.
